CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 1, 1962, pg. 28, reads: "Homestead Tippers - One of the best softball aggregations in Pennsylvania is the Homestead Tippers of Homestead, Pa.  The team, sponsored by well-known sportsman Milton (Coast) Bunt, compiled an outstanding record this year.  Left to right, front row: Mike Jackson, Lawrence Thompson, Ronald Dulin, Ronald Blunt, William Corbett and Gene Lightner.  Second row:  Milton Blunt, manager; Clarence Ward, Harvey Freeman, Dorothy Kelly, team's booster; Jerome Dent and Ted Brown.  Back row: Donald Waller, Frank Waller, Kenny Batts, Al Goodman and Juice Lance. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Homestead Tippers softball team, front row from left: Mike Jackson, Lawrence Thompson, Ronald Dulin, Ronald Blunt, William Corbett, Gene Lightner; second row: manager Milton "Coast" Blount, Clarence Ward, Harvey Freeman, booster Dorothy Kelly, Jerome Dent, Ted Brown; back row: Donald Waller, Frank Waller, Kenny Batts, Al Goodman, and Juice Lance, posed in front of 600 Bar, Homestead
